



His Excellenc
Amsterdam the 4 Jul 1782



By Capt: Trowbridge arrived from Boston received  Letter from our Mutual friend M. Isaak Smith1 with Two Bills on the Honnourable Henry Laurens Esqe. for bf550. Each which presmed to present your Excellenc for Acceptance and request to retrn the Same.
At same Time Shall be Obliged to your Excellenc to be Informed where to present the six Bills for payment falling due the 4 of next Month.
[155]
I am on all Occasions with the profoundest Esteem and Consideration His Excellenc Your Most Obd: & Much Obligd Servt

John Hodshon

